rComments: He comes across as pretty timid when he's teaching, which makes the class atmosphere feel a little strange. He does mark relatively easy; if you show up and do the work, you'll likely get a good grade. Grading criteria is not always clear, and feedback is not always helpful. He's knowledgable and a good prof, and he shows respect to students.

Kyle is new to teaching and it shows in his confidence while teaching. Despite being new, he is knowledgeable on the subject. I'll be honest, I skipped a few classes, but over all it didnt make too much of a difference. Im sure if I tried just a little more I wouldve gotten an A. I learnt more about sound and lighting with him than with Jon

Not super clear about expectations. He is easy though - show up, put in a little effort, and it's easy to get an A+. Very sassy, but not in a funny way. Lectures are boring and labs are a bit better, but not great.
